tspan.tspan: Note: This is not a full project, just the outline of an idea. Use it as a starting point, but go further, be more complete and careful.
You're expected to do your own literature search on the topic.
The famous "cheerios effect" is what happens when two cheerios in your bowl of milk get close together: they attract each
other and collide! In this project you will analyse this effect using video recording and tracking, with the goal of checking the
published theory for the separation distance

tspan.tspan: This started with actual cheerios mostly because that's the name of the effect - but cheerios make a poor object (they're all different,
they get soggy after a short time, they're not spheres). So try different objects. Does their size matter? What else has an effect? Can
you replicate Vella and Mahadevan's (2005) experimental work? Can you find the force between the cheerios and how it depends on
distance? What else can you explore here?
